entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i see what you mean how easy was it for you to get used to living in la

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: pretty easy

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good what are some things that make you really mad

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: h i would say people are rude not having enough money what else just a lot of things are frustrating i guess

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what do you do when you are annoyed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i guess it depends on what i am annoyed about like if it is at another person or about something i did or just life in general

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: can you give me an example of that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: if somebody like a person annoys me i will probably let them know they are annoying me until they stop

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: h

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: is that what you are talking about

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay yes

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: okay

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: when was the last time you felt really happy

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: h maybe like six months ago

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me more about that

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: things were just going really well did not have much stress in my life

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you noticed any changes in your behavior or thoughts lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah i am i am easier more easily irritated and yell more tired more kind of down feeling down more not as productive

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you been diagnosed with depression

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah awhile ago

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how long ago were you diagnosed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: h do not know exactly it is been a few years but i still feel the same as i did when they diagnosed me so i asse i am still depressed

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what got you to seek help

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: well i just i am a big believer in talking to people about your problems so i just thought that would be a good idea so i did it and and that is what i found out

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you feel like therapy is useful

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: oh yeah definitely
